<subSubSection id="C35A6562FFC0FFA7FF4BFDA57D817264" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BFF36E9FFC0FFA7FF4BFDA57D817264" blockId="4.[168,775,589,815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B934EAFBFFC0FFA7FF4BFDA57D15732E" bold="true" box="[168,285,589,613]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
this species is characterized by the following combination of characters: slender body, its depth equal to or shorter than head length; mouth protruding downwards; small slender teeth on both jaws; anterior dorsolateral surface of body and breast completely scaled; anterior spinous dorsal fin without conspicuous black blotch (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B18FFC0FFA7FF1AFCFF7D767264" author="Senou H" box="[249,382,791,815]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" pagination="1995 - 1998" refId="ref7218" refString="Senou H (2013) Leiognathidae. In: Nakabo T (Ed.) Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species, 3 rd edition. Tokai University Press, Hadano, 900 - 904, 1995 - 1998." type="journal article" year="2013">Senou 2013</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A6562FFC0FFA7FF4BFCA07E0E75C5" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BFF36E9FFC0FFA7FF4BFCA07E0E75C5" blockId="4.[168,775,840,1166]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">
<emphasis id="B934EAFBFFC0FFA7FF4BFCA07CF072C9" inLineHeading="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B934EAFBFFC0FFA7FF4BFCA07D32722B" bold="true" box="[168,314,840,864]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C404D6AFFC0FFA7FEA3FCA07DED722B" baseAuthorityName="Whitley" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[320,485,840,864]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Leiognathidae" genus="Equulites" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="popei">
<emphasis id="B934EAFBFFC0FFA7FEA3FCA07DED722B" box="[320,485,840,864]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Equulites popei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FD69FCA17EC1722B" box="[650,713,841,864]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Japan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FD30FCA07CF072C9" name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Philippines</collectingCountry>
</emphasis>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FEE7FC827D6E72C9" box="[260,358,874,898]" name="Malaysia" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="4984F80BFFC0FFA7FE95FC827DB472C9" box="[374,444,874,898]" country="Malaysia" name="Sabah" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Sabah</collectingRegion>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FE33FC827E2772C9" box="[464,559,874,898]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Thailand</collectingCountry>
(Gulf of 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FD7BFC827EF372C9" box="[664,763,874,898]" name="Thailand" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Thailand</collectingCountry>
), 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FF4BFC637CE472E8" box="[168,236,907,931]" name="Oman" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Oman</collectingCountry>
, the Red Sea including Suez Bay, the Mediterranean (immigrant from the Red Sea), and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FF4BFC267D3072AD" box="[168,312,974,998]" name="Mozambique" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Mozambique</collectingCountry>
. In Japanese waters, this species is known from the Noto Peninsula, Sea of 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FDEBFC187E4D754C" box="[520,581,1008,1031]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Japan</collectingCountry>
coast of 
<collectingRegion id="4984F80BFFC0FFA7FD45FC187D4B7562" country="Japan" name="Yamaguchi" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Yamaguchi Prefecture</collectingRegion>
, western coast of Kyushu (Sea of 
<collectingCountry id="F3577679FFC0FFA7FD29FBFA7F0F7562" box="[714,775,1042,1065]" name="Japan" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Japan</collectingCountry>
coast), Sagami Bay to the southern part of eastern coast of Kyushu (Pacific coast), and 
<collectingRegion id="4984F80BFFC0FFA7FDE6FBBC7E6D7527" box="[517,613,1108,1132]" country="Japan" name="Okinawa" pageId="4" pageNumber="247">Okinawa</collectingRegion>
Island (
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B18FFC0FFA7FD20FBBD7CE875C5" author="Senou H" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" pagination="1995 - 1998" refId="ref7218" refString="Senou H (2013) Leiognathidae. In: Nakabo T (Ed.) Fishes of Japan with Pictorial Keys to the Species, 3 rd edition. Tokai University Press, Hadano, 900 - 904, 1995 - 1998." type="journal article" year="2013">Senou 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFD14B18FFC0FFA7FF08FB9E7DF375C5" author="Suzuki H &amp; Kimura S" box="[235,507,1142,1166]" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" pagination="339 - 352" refId="ref7316" refString="Suzuki H, Kimura S (2017) Taxonomic revision of the Equulites elongatu s (Gunther 1874) species group (Perciformes: Leiognathidae) with the description of a new species. Ichthyological Research 64 (3): 339 - 352. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 017 - 0572 - 9" type="journal article" year="2017">Suzuki and Kimura 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C35A6562FFC0FFA7FF4BFB407DA37448" pageId="4" pageNumber="247" type="discussion">
